<node id="&quot;DAMAGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Compensation sought by a litigant in a lawsuit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Damages are monetary compensation for losses claimed by or against the State."&lt;SEP&gt;"Damages are the financial losses resulting from noncompliance, which are hard to quantify."&lt;SEP&gt;"Damages refer to financial losses suffered by the Department due to a breach of the subsection, which are inherently difficult to quantify."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Department may recover additional damages beyond those covered by the $50,000 credit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Department may recover damages resulting from the Contractor’s failure to act."&lt;SEP&gt;"The credits are exclusive of any other right to damages."</data>
