  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A Member is a person defined as a 'health plan member' under subsection 110.123(2)(e) of Florida Statutes."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Member is a person defined as a health plan member under Florida Statutes."&lt;SEP&gt;"A Member is a person who is enrolled and is the primary insured, as defined in Florida law."&lt;SEP&gt;"A member is an individual enrolled in the disease management program who requires care and management."&lt;SEP&gt;"A participant who may request a mailed copy of the SPD."&lt;SEP&gt;"A person affected by a breach or incident."&lt;SEP&gt;"An individual who files a lawsuit against Contractor regarding eligibility, enrollment, or coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Members with specific issues are referred to the most experienced nurse for that condition."&lt;SEP&gt;"Members with specific issues are referred to the most experienced nurse for their condition."</data>
