<node id="&quot;ACCESS CRITERIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"STANDARD"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Access criteria are the benchmarks that must be met (or attempted) for section 7.3 to be exercised."&lt;SEP&gt;"Access criteria are the benchmarks that must be met (or attempted) for section 7.3 to be triggered."&lt;SEP&gt;"Access criteria are the benchmarks that the Contractor must meet, and their fulfillment triggers the Department's right to act under section 7.3."&lt;SEP&gt;"Access criteria are the specific requirements that Contractors must strive to meet."&lt;SEP&gt;"Access criteria may not be fully met, even with good faith efforts, as acknowledged by the Department."&lt;SEP&gt;"The access criteria are specific requirements that the Contractor is expected to meet. They are identified in the contract and are central to determining whether section 7.3 can be exercised."&lt;SEP&gt;"The access criteria may not be fully met by the Contractor, despite good faith efforts, as recognized by the Department."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-536bb3f69282f0b1683044e52fc49ca7</data>
</node>
