<node id="&quot;FLORIDA STATUTES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Florida Statutes are the codified laws of the state of Florida, defining key terms used in the contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes are the codified laws of the state of Florida, specifically sections 287.133, 287.134, and 287.137, which govern vendor restrictions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes contain the legal basis for requiring liquidated damages."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes is the body of law that includes section 119.0701."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes is the legal framework under which the Contract may be extended."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes, particularly section 110.123(9), are referenced as a source of legal authority for the protection of State of Florida Data."&lt;SEP&gt;"Florida Statutes, specifically section 110.123(5)(g), governs the requirement for written notice to Participants regarding unpaid provider payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"State laws of Florida that govern the handling of proprietary, trade secret, and confidential data."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Florida Statutes are a body of state laws, and section 110.123 specifically governs aspects of the Contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"The body of laws in the state of Florida, including section 627.642, which governs ID Card compliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"The codified laws of the state of Florida, including section 20.055(5)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3c767c42c4e19b535729414ef8d73ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b57b1f6f75687090fceb29727cfad251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e6bf92f0ea1c6258861ff1086796ace&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42eb7824bc4b6dae1f55110a76cae692&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ac2c9a651e12d0bbc80acf2a9565c92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21fd01b6cf2ffac2e48390b9e584cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-042bc330a3f245f87e013cf42b730533&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70f9e1425a666eea901041c636a75607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a27bbe9186e0b89c85dff042c6e2c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c29476b54ecf1664862eece0459c63e6</data>
</node>
