<node id="&quot;LIQUIDATED DAMAGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Liquidated damages are a pre-agreed sum intended to compensate for unknown and unascertainable damages, not to serve as a penalty."&lt;SEP&gt;"Liquidated damages are a pre-agreed sum to compensate for unquantifiable losses due to noncompliance."&lt;SEP&gt;"Liquidated damages are a pre-determined amount payable by the Contractor when performance guarantees are not met, intended to cover internal staffing and administrative costs and diminished service value."&lt;SEP&gt;"Liquidated damages are pre-agreed damages specified in the Contract."&lt;SEP&gt;"Liquidated damages are specified in Section 7 of the Contract and apply if the Awarded Respondent fails to meet the milestone of being 100% operational by the implementation date."&lt;SEP&gt;"Pre-determined penalties for failure to meet milestones."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Contractor must pay liquidated damages if Minimum Service Requirements are not met."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Contractor pays $10,000 per calendar day for each unmet deadline."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Contractor pays $10,000 per calendar day until the deadline is met."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Department considers whether the Contractor has been subject to liquidated damages in complying with Contract requirements."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Department considers whether the Contractor has been subject to liquidated damages."&lt;SEP&gt;"The credits are classified as liquidated damages, not penalties."&lt;SEP&gt;"The credits are in the nature of liquidated damages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d03da7ad0a2c45bd8acfaa3e7086933e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa3b36fea58d72059cd585dada27264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21fd01b6cf2ffac2e48390b9e584cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86d51fd3dc4466f1769637ccb655bea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973b86edc6f84e59f50507a111e8afca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be8d8979403f6066066c55d416f7a095&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a27bbe9186e0b89c85dff042c6e2c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ced7b0d6c3e25b1f766368ff30d9f7db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80197926c45627b0efe3aa47310d15c0</data>
</node>
