<node id="&quot;DISEASE MANAGEMENT PROGRAM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROGRAM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A program designed to manage members' health conditions, where one nurse may manage multiple members' conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A program that enables centralized management of multiple patient conditions by a single nurse."&lt;SEP&gt;"A program that includes coordination with PCPs and treating physicians."&lt;SEP&gt;"A structured program designed to manage multiple disease states in patients, involving coordinated interactions and interventions."&lt;SEP&gt;"A structured program that enables centralized nursing management of multiple patient conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Department may choose to implement a Disease Management program, requiring cooperation from the Awarded Respondent."&lt;SEP&gt;"The Disease Management Program is overseen by the Associate Medical Director of Clinical Quality."&lt;SEP&gt;"The medical director is involved in program oversight, approval, monitoring, and quality improvement."</data>
