<node id="&quot;CONTRACT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">The CONTRACT is a legally binding, formal agreement between the Department and the Contractor, serving as the primary legal document governing their relationship. It outlines the terms, conditions, obligations, responsibilities, and compliance requirements for the provision of services, particularly in the context of disease management services, including potential integration of new disease states. The agreement defines the scope of services, the manner in which they must be performed, and the specific deliverables to be provided, with all such deliverables subject to the Department’s right to conduct audits of the Contractor and any subcontractors. The CONTRACT is a comprehensive legal instrument that governs all transactions and interactions between the parties, including access to State of Florida Data, and remains the property of the State, requiring return upon termination or within 16 months thereafter.

The Contractor is obligated to perform work in accordance with the agreed-upon terms, including timely performance, especially on the Effective Date and for Performance Guarantees. The agreement includes provisions related to charges, costs, and expenses, and specifies the only payments allowed for use of deliverables. It also prohibits certain actions, such as travel expense bills, unauthorized transfers, and subcontracting or employment restrictions, and requires prior written approval from the Department for any such activities. The CONTRACT further restricts participation to only directly approved persons or entities and prohibits the Contractor from engaging in business in certain countries or boycotting Israel, with termination possible under specific conditions, including false certification or being on restricted company lists.

The CONTRACT includes provisions for the retention and transfer of public records upon completion, with the agreement specifying the scope of records to be retained and the obligation to transfer them to the public agency. It also governs the duration and conditions of meetings, including post-termination obligations, and must be terminated before the obligation to maintain services begins. The agreement was awarded based on the Contractor’s business representation and is the full and complete contract between the parties, excluding certain provisions of PUR 1000. The CONTRACT may not prohibit the disclosure of relevant information, and notices are issued regarding its administration. The agreement is subject to legal and administrative proceedings, and its breach may result in enforcement actions. The Contractor may reference the CONTRACT as an experience citation with other customers without prior approval, but all other aspects of the agreement remain strictly governed by its terms.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-63f578d53bfa5cd1841300ebfaf269bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7e6a516b7850b1520d99188994c12b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973e4e5caf2d5df7a31230aa09be9f8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a5052451843bac89ec6d46e7bd8593f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7009d4e99c1b1b5f2db7b0b27c5aab50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8484f7b881e4e7cbe9759b6862d56796&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a27bbe9186e0b89c85dff042c6e2c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756bf9cd6cba13a690d1a1ab1ca15ac8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-929f90597b1751dba1a9fd1a32b051bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e76ed74a8f332bb4b0ce48da988e36a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87aacb2e5a1d425f139e7028172e5302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd1ed5d9ddc784a0f14b59a08c792ef1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa3b36fea58d72059cd585dada27264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-042bc330a3f245f87e013cf42b730533&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e260eaaa7468bbb26e412849c414e7b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70f9e1425a666eea901041c636a75607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c767c42c4e19b535729414ef8d73ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7c62733ea576c9deceb35110683bdd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f96bc837864e7d2f0162d851756dde37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42eb7824bc4b6dae1f55110a76cae692&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf38bec4792e1237dac8580ddd00b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-18ed6bd678bd05e4b28c9ca879edceda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8cdf71ba9cb5fec13698ef864b45b43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb25811043bde746cec405019a7c28d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b254c4b63c9acf3eabfaab008c51ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d64fe1d6f1d848dfb8c74c71b18155&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d4223fbc24b29d99308c28ad9b7af66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f845aab9b03b9209585da5582e15baa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7be865cd763682914359f37abc6f55c3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AWARDED RESPONDENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">The Awarded Respondent is the entity awarded the contract to administer the health plan, responsible for providing comprehensive services and ensuring compliance with all contractual obligations, state regulations, and HIPAA requirements. It is responsible for achieving full operational status by January 1, 2024, at 12:00:00 A.M., and is liable for liquidated damages under Section 7 of the Contract if this milestone is not met. The Awarded Respondent operates all functions and systems relevant to the Department and the Plan, including maintaining a national healthcare provider network, managing participant information, issuing ID cards under specified conditions, and maintaining the SSN as the record number.

The Awarded Respondent is responsible for establishing and performing all aspects of claims processing, including coordination of benefits, claims reimbursement, point-of-sale transactions, claim adjudication, and payment, ensuring claims are processed with primary and secondary payers without involving the participant. It must assign dedicated personnel for the Department, including a claims supervisor, claims facility, billing manager, eligibility manager, and dedicated claims processors/adjustors. It must also maintain a dedicated Customer Service Unit composed of full-time, non-contracted employees and ensure an adequate number of incoming telephone lines for participant and pharmacy/provider inquiries, including a 24/7/365 clinician-staffed toll-free line for all Plan Participants.

The Awarded Respondent is responsible for developing all Plan-related printed materials at no additional cost, delivering them in a culturally and linguistically appropriate manner, and submitting all materials to the Department for approval before distribution. It must establish an interactive website, provide unlimited online access to its systems and data to Department users, and maintain an online directory of network providers. It must also provide temporary ID cards via a dedicated website and issue additional ID cards upon participant request.

The Awarded Respondent must conduct background checks as required by Section 4.2.4 of the Contract, perform a pre-implementation audit of 200–300 manually created claims, test eligibility files, and review key procedures and controls. It must diligently work to deliver a satisfactory Implementation Plan, submit a draft agenda five business days before each meeting for Department approval, and submit the final Implementation Plan to the Department. It must also participate in all readiness assessment activities before the Implementation Date, benefit fairs, and meetings organized by the Department during the Fall 2023 Open Enrollment period, including all locations of the annual</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5c4a9169533286ec9e7cbfc255165a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2800a47e9bda55f14b649f4433087f95&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e26053d9354d3bcc7560c305bbe1012&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be8d8979403f6066066c55d416f7a095&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ced7b0d6c3e25b1f766368ff30d9f7db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756bf9cd6cba13a690d1a1ab1ca15ac8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db666e270f96718db00f123739d57c9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a21de729aeac2ac5411293b5eb7a85b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87aacb2e5a1d425f139e7028172e5302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd1ed5d9ddc784a0f14b59a08c792ef1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7afb47b665f9a355360d8f19b072515d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a15086157f2c790665924983ad25ad5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e260eaaa7468bbb26e412849c414e7b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7c62733ea576c9deceb35110683bdd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9aaa428a9cedb15e5c65db44f369179&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b57b1f6f75687090fceb29727cfad251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf38bec4792e1237dac8580ddd00b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d72ea75fb519c8242ca877027c6dc469&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c29476b54ecf1664862eece0459c63e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc984120e1f1f604e806000ba1bb8141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-902137132fe9e53d1a269692b4827557&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f072e3015b0ae8c04fcad41e822dbe34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-634b420b1dffb2db682f1098aa431f4e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEPARTMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">The DEPARTMENT, formally known as the Florida Department of Management Services (DMS) or its designee—including third-party administrators contracted under Florida Statutes—is a state governmental entity and the primary contracting party responsible for overseeing the administration, compliance, and performance of health plan contracts, including the HMO contract awarded to the Contractor for Region Two. As a key governmental and regulatory body, the DEPARTMENT holds full and final decision-making authority over eligibility, coverage, benefits, claims, and the interpretation of the Benefits Document. It is the entity that awards, manages, and enforces the contract, with sole discretion to renew, modify, suspend, or terminate the agreement, provided 60 days’ written notice is given. The DEPARTMENT is also the party that may initiate legal actions, must be notified of any legal proceedings involving the Plan, and is protected, defended, and indemnified by the Contractor.

The DEPARTMENT is responsible for approving the Implementation Plan, evaluating its sufficiency, and determining whether it meets required standards. It has the authority to approve or reject all Plan-related printed materials, including the annual Benefits Guide, the benefit website, the ID card design, the EOB design, appeal-related communications, and the SPD, requiring prior written approval for all such materials. It also approves the design and content of the website, the finalized billing and financial processes, and the insurance coverage before performance can begin. The DEPARTMENT must approve any assignment, publication of engagement results, significant system changes, and public dissemination of contract information, and it may unilaterally require changes via written change order.

As a regulatory and oversight body, the DEPARTMENT has broad authority to audit, inspect, and review all aspects of the Contractor’s and subcontractors’ activities. This includes the right to conduct performance and compliance audits, inspect working areas, computer systems, and facilities, request access to accounting records, and audit the Contractor’s background screening process with two days’ prior written notice. It may request audio recordings of calls within three business days, demand disclosure of written policies and information at any time, and request documentation, testimony, and data submissions in specified formats and frequencies. The DEPARTMENT may also request non-routine updates, set completion timelines, and require in-person, virtual, or telephonic appearances for review or appeal hearings.

The DEPARTMENT is responsible for issuing the Invitation to Negotiate (ITN) No. DMS22/23-072, coordinating benefit fairs</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-5c4a9169533286ec9e7cbfc255165a4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-63f578d53bfa5cd1841300ebfaf269bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7e6a516b7850b1520d99188994c12b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973e4e5caf2d5df7a31230aa09be9f8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bb11a44dfb0a8eaa9a9252f491073e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e6bf92f0ea1c6258861ff1086796ace&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e26053d9354d3bcc7560c305bbe1012&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-969e870a5811ebdf4707b674630d71ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ac2c9a651e12d0bbc80acf2a9565c92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c3ef80760569a1309bf119b6ff80c702&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7009d4e99c1b1b5f2db7b0b27c5aab50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86d51fd3dc4466f1769637ccb655bea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973b86edc6f84e59f50507a111e8afca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8484f7b881e4e7cbe9759b6862d56796&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7be865cd763682914359f37abc6f55c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a27bbe9186e0b89c85dff042c6e2c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-be8d8979403f6066066c55d416f7a095&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c6726c4bcf6c7394361d6ad2fcf3002&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f9ddff393a5a6ceeb66f094e647f7fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-756bf9cd6cba13a690d1a1ab1ca15ac8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ced7b0d6c3e25b1f766368ff30d9f7db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-929f90597b1751dba1a9fd1a32b051bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db666e270f96718db00f123739d57c9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a21de729aeac2ac5411293b5eb7a85b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e76ed74a8f332bb4b0ce48da988e36a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-87aacb2e5a1d425f139e7028172e5302&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd1ed5d9ddc784a0f14b59a08c792ef1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7afb47b665f9a355360d8f19b072515d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a15086157f2c790665924983ad25ad5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa3b36fea58d72059cd585dada27264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-042bc330a3f245f87e013cf42b730533&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-536bb3f69282f0b1683044e52fc49ca7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e260eaaa7468bbb26e412849c414e7b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70f9e1425a666eea901041c636a75607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c767c42c4e19b535729414ef8d73ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c9aaa428a9cedb15e5c65db44f369179&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f96bc837864e7d2f0162d851756dde37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7c62733ea576c9deceb35110683bdd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e186e17653b287e3cfa5f205a6520f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80197926c45627b0efe3aa47310d15c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b57b1f6f75687090fceb29727cfad251&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9b2fbc62ea8c019a8196a95956dc5b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42eb7824bc4b6dae1f55110a76cae692&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cebd27b76b8ffb6789a18f25f37456f7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adf38bec4792e1237dac8580ddd00b04&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d72ea75fb519c8242ca877027c6dc469&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21fd01b6cf2ffac2e48390b9e584cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb25811043bde746cec405019a7c28d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f27e3efb4e453bfd444a2596a8c9623f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c29476b54ecf1664862eece0459c63e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b254c4b63c9acf3eabfaab008c51ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-112e64f1bb6118d9bccd195e08f5f314&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79a76389ae9d41ad98c308997796bb27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc984120e1f1f604e806000ba1bb8141&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d03da7ad0a2c45bd8acfaa3e7086933e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-902137132fe9e53d1a269692b4827557&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d64fe1d6f1d848dfb8c74c71b18155&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f072e3015b0ae8c04fcad41e822dbe34&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d4223fbc24b29d99308c28ad9b7af66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-634b420b1dffb2db682f1098aa431f4e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22732b1682f394a948fe66cb5abaee05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f845aab9b03b9209585da5582e15baa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5a9d5f35482c8cebfb35f593b3063da</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CONTRACTOR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">The Contractor, identified as Capital Health Plan, Inc., is an organization that responded to the Department’s Invitation to Negotiate and was awarded the HMO contract for Region Two through the ITN process. As the primary party responsible for fulfilling the terms of the contract, the Contractor is an independent contractor, including its agents, subcontractors, officers, and employees, and retains the legal status of an independent entity. The Contractor is responsible for delivering services as defined in the contract, including providing all labor, materials, and supplies for the Services in Region 2, and must perform these services in accordance with the Implementation Plan, meeting all deadlines and performance guarantees.

The Contractor is obligated to comply with all applicable laws, rules, codes, ordinances, and licensing requirements, including federal, state, and local regulations, HIPAA, Section 508 accessibility standards, and Florida Statutes related to confidentiality and data protection. It must ensure that all personnel, including subcontractors, are screened for criminal background checks, with screenings refreshed every five years during the contract term. The Contractor must also conduct or ensure criminal background screenings for all individuals operating under its direction and investigate whether any person with a disqualifying offense should continue services or retain access to State of Florida Data.

The Contractor is responsible for protecting, defending, and indemnifying the Department against claims related to its determination of confidentiality, professional liability, errors or omissions, and breaches of confidential personal information. It must create and maintain a written policy for the protection of State of Florida Data, document and record each instance of access to such data, and take immediate action to protect the data from further unauthorized access upon discovery of a breach or incident. The Contractor must notify the Department immediately upon discovering a breach, incident, unauthorized access, unauthorized transmission, or suspicion of a material violation, and must set up a conference call upon becoming aware of such events.

The Contractor is prohibited from subcontracting services or changing approved subcontractors without prior written notice and Department approval. It may use subcontractors to deliver services but remains fully liable for the acts or omissions of all subcontractors, agents, and employees. The Contractor must not employ or subcontract with State employees or individuals involved in the contract’s performance and must not knowingly employ unauthorized aliens in performing work under the contract. It must use E-Verify for all newly hired employees and must not perform services outside the U.S. or transmit Florida Data abroad.

The Contractor is subject to audits and inspections by the Department, including</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-63f578d53bfa5cd1841300ebfaf269bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7e6a516b7850b1520d99188994c12b7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973e4e5caf2d5df7a31230aa09be9f8d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d8bc7fada8f87797f63efcdf326ef70&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2bb11a44dfb0a8eaa9a9252f491073e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0e6bf92f0ea1c6258861ff1086796ace&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a5052451843bac89ec6d46e7bd8593f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2ac2c9a651e12d0bbc80acf2a9565c92&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7009d4e99c1b1b5f2db7b0b27c5aab50&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-86d51fd3dc4466f1769637ccb655bea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-973b86edc6f84e59f50507a111e8afca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8484f7b881e4e7cbe9759b6862d56796&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7be865cd763682914359f37abc6f55c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3a27bbe9186e0b89c85dff042c6e2c65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f9ddff393a5a6ceeb66f094e647f7fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-929f90597b1751dba1a9fd1a32b051bc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e76ed74a8f332bb4b0ce48da988e36a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eaa3b36fea58d72059cd585dada27264&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5a72372edcc1dfb0acb871dae0e77775&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-042bc330a3f245f87e013cf42b730533&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-536bb3f69282f0b1683044e52fc49ca7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70f9e1425a666eea901041c636a75607&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c767c42c4e19b535729414ef8d73ee8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a7c62733ea576c9deceb35110683bdd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f96bc837864e7d2f0162d851756dde37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e186e17653b287e3cfa5f205a6520f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80197926c45627b0efe3aa47310d15c0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9b2fbc62ea8c019a8196a95956dc5b2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-42eb7824bc4b6dae1f55110a76cae692&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8cdf71ba9cb5fec13698ef864b45b43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bb21fd01b6cf2ffac2e48390b9e584cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb25811043bde746cec405019a7c28d2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f27e3efb4e453bfd444a2596a8c9623f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7b254c4b63c9acf3eabfaab008c51ce0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-79a76389ae9d41ad98c308997796bb27&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d03da7ad0a2c45bd8acfaa3e7086933e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8d64fe1d6f1d848dfb8c74c71b18155&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d4223fbc24b29d99308c28ad9b7af66&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22732b1682f394a948fe66cb5abaee05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f845aab9b03b9209585da5582e15baa7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b5a9d5f35482c8cebfb35f593b3063da</data>
</node>
